            {
              "id": 898073,
              "key": "f37553d1-ac64-49f9-a60f-ee442b7edd9e",
              "title": null,
              "semantic_type": "TextAtom",
              "is_public": true,
              "text": "We will first look at unit testing REST APIs using <a href=\"https://junit.org/junit5/\">JUnit</a>, <a href=\"https://site.mockito.org/\">Mockito</a> and <a href=\"https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/test/web/servlet/MockMvc.html\">Spring Test</a> (also known as, MockMVC).\n\n<ul>\n<li>JUnit is a popular unit testing framework that allows you to test individual units of source code.</li>\n<li>Mockito is a great mocking framework which provices data for JUnit tests. </li>\n<li><code>@MockBean</code> works well with the Mockito library.</li>\n<li><code>@WebMvcTest</code> is used for controller layer unit testing. </li>\n</ul>\n",
              "instructor_notes": ""
            },
            {
